# Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) Configuration
# Required when STORAGE_PROVIDER=oracle
# 
# IMPORTANT: Each OCID has a specific format. Make sure you're using the correct one!
#
# 1. Tenancy OCID: 
#    - Location: OCI Console → Identity → Tenancy Details → OCID
#    - Format: MUST start with "ocid1.tenancy.oc1."
#    - Example: ocid1.tenancy.oc1..aaaaaaaa...
#
# 2. User OCID: 
#    - Location: OCI Console → Identity → Users → [Your User] → OCID
#    - Format: MUST start with "ocid1.user.oc1."
#    - Example: ocid1.user.oc1..aaaaaaaa...
#    - ⚠️  DO NOT use bucket OCID, namespace, or any other OCID here!
#
# 3. Fingerprint: 
#    - Location: OCI Console → Identity → Users → [Your User] → API Keys → Fingerprint
#    - Format: 16 hex pairs separated by colons
#    - Example: aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff:00:11:22:33:44:55:66:77:88:99
#
# 4. Private Key: 
#    - The private key file content (from the API key pair you created)
#    - Must use \n for newlines (see format below)
#
# 5. Region: 
#    - Examples: us-ashburn-1, us-phoenix-1, ap-mumbai-1, eu-frankfurt-1
#    - Find in OCI Console → Region selector (top right)
#
# 6. Namespace: 
#    - Location: OCI Console → Object Storage → Bucket Details → Namespace
#    - This is a STRING (not an OCID), usually alphanumeric
#
# 7. Bucket Name: 
#    - Your bucket name in Object Storage
#    - This is a STRING (not an OCID), just the bucket name
#
OCI_TENANCY_OCID=ocid1.tenancy.oc1..aaaaaaaa...
OCI_USER_OCID=ocid1.user.oc1..aaaaaaaa...
OCI_FINGERPRINT=aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff:00:11:22:33:44:55:66:77:88:99
OCI_REGION=ap-mumbai-1
OCI_NAMESPACE=your-namespace
OCI_BUCKET_NAME=your-bucket-name
# Private key content (the entire key including BEGIN/END lines, use \n for newlines)
# IMPORTANT: The entire value must be on ONE line with \n for newlines, and wrapped in quotes
# Example format:
OCI_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\nMIIEpAIBAAKCAQEA...\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----"
# Or without quotes if no special characters at the start (but quotes are safer):
# OCI_PRIVATE_KEY=-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\nMIIEpAIBAAKCAQEA...\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----
# Optional: Passphrase if your private key is encrypted
OCI_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSPHRASE=

